description: Dimensions: B fg. 4.0; H fg 1.8; depth e. bevel 7; t e. bev 0.5,  Typology: body wafer thin and consistent in thickness; sharp angles inside flanges with virt. vert. walls & v. sl. convex outer faces,  Manufacture: fg. sides rippled - pres. hmks.; v. sl. angular shoulders in sides at base of fgs. (indicated by arrows on illus.) suggest some if not all of fg. created in forging; faint bev. on either face at butt echoes butt line; bl. e. on one face with faint and slight irreg. double bevel - upper one tending to disappear in centre; hints only of sim. on rev.; scattered isolated hmks. here and higher on body; sl. skew from bl. e. to butt,  Condition: bl. e. thin but not v. sharp - small indents, some prob. anc.; butt v. thin  and undam.; coppery gold flecking along very crests of fgs. and a little of butt & bl. e. - recent rubbing & no significant dam. associated; 'V' shaped depression in rev. of one bl. tip - either flaked surface or caused in manu.;

T. 9.0 ; wt 335.8 g,  Typology:,  Faces appear to have been virt. flat in cross section - sides slightly bowed poss with tendency to double facetting - but no crisp bevel extant ; intact body angles fairly crisp with minimal lipping in evidence; certainly no central bevel; despite loss of sur. but had evid. been pretty thin.,  Manufacture:,  Evid. for moderately set e. bev. - crest of bevel just perceptible in spots; some monor asymmetry in provilfe - but slightly flattter face is more curved close to butt than is reverse.  ,  Condition:,  No indication of dam. prior to corrosion etc. ; score/rub marks down either butt side & file ripples across either butt side, all assoc. with gold flecking - modern interference by finder and his colleagues ; none of c.e. intact,  Attached material:,  v. little trace of yellow soil, in one case forming accretion like spot with admixture of white grains (calcium?)
